{"parentUuid":"a7deb8e6-47c6-48da-869a-a95166ddb200","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"ad2e30b85cc1c5b90","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0188RBdKJjCV8G1V8Lj1tPyb","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Darwin Godel Machine Sakana AI arxiv paper self-improving\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Darwin-Gödel Machine: The First Self-Improving AI System Is Here\",\"url\":\"https://www.intoai.pub/p/darwin-godel-machine-the-first-self\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - lemoz/darwin-godel-machine: Self-improving AI agents implementing the Darwin Gödel Machine research paper. Features multi-LLM support, sandboxed execution, population-based evolution, and comprehensive benchmarking.\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/lemoz/darwin-godel-machine\"},{\"title\":\"Darwin Gödel Machine: Self-Improving AI Agents - AI Papers Academy\",\"url\":\"https://aipapersacademy.com/darwin-godel-machine/\"},{\"title\":\"Open ended algorithms: inside sakana’s darwin gödel machine | by Rick Boelen | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://medium.com/@rickboelen98/open-ended-algorithms-inside-sakanas-darwin-g%C3%B6del-machine-a129a5fe5379\"},{\"title\":\"Sakana AI on X: \\\"Introducing The Darwin Gödel Machine: AI that improves itself by rewriting its own code https://t.co/tBzlhoUMZO The Darwin Gödel Machine (DGM) is a self-improving agent that can modify its own code. Inspired by evolution, we maintain an expanding lineage of agent variants, https://t.co/yIQ0w85N7U\\\" / X\",\"url\":\"https://x.com/SakanaAILabs/status/1928272612431646943\"},{\"title\":\"The Darwin Gödel Machine: Open-Ended Improvement via Recursive Code Mutation and Empirical Fitness | by Adnan Masood, PhD. | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://medium.com/@adnanmasood/the-darwin-g%C3%B6del-machine-open-ended-improvement-via-recursive-code-mutation-and-empirical-fitness-a777681d73e4\"},{\"title\":\"Darwin Gödel Machine - by Grigory Sapunov - Gonzo ML\",\"url\":\"https://gonzoml.substack.com/p/darwin-godel-machine\"},{\"title\":\"Darwin Godel Machine: Open-Ended Evolution of Self-Improving Agents\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2505.22954\"},{\"title\":\"[2505.22954] Darwin Godel Machine: Open-Ended Evolution of Self-Improving Agents\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2505.22954\"},{\"title\":\"The Darwin Gödel Machine: AI that improves itself by rewriting its own code\",\"url\":\"https://sakana.ai/dgm/\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about the Darwin Gödel Machine paper:\n\n## Overview\n\nThe Darwin Gödel Machine (DGM) is a paper authored by Jenny Zhang and 4 other authors that introduces a self-improving AI system. The research paper is titled \"Darwin Gödel Machine: Open-Ended Evolution of Self-Improving Agents\" and is available on arXiv (arXiv:2505.22954).\n\n## What It Does\n\nThe Darwin-Gödel Machine is an architecture that can iteratively modify its own codebase to improve itself while continuously checking its performance on different coding benchmarks. This architecture is inspired by Darwinian evolutionary biology, in which multiple variants grow from a single starting point and the ones that perform the best \"survive\" most successfully.\n\n## Key Innovation\n\nThe DGM relaxes the Gödel Machine's impractical requirement of theoretically proving that a change will improve the system, instead requiring empirical evidence from experiments to demonstrate that a proposed new version enhances performance.\n\n## Results\n\nThe DGM automatically improves its coding capabilities, increasing performance on SWE-bench from 20.0% to 50.0%, and on Polyglot from 14.2% to 30.7%.\n\n## Team\n\nResearchers at Sakana AI, a Tokyo-based AI research lab, proposed this architecture, and the work was done in collaboration with Jeff Clune's lab at the University of British Columbia.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"49c785e9-2a53-4890-bd71-32d7e76ed0f2","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:34:13.678Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"Darwin Godel Machine Sakana AI arxiv paper self-improving","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01Whnsd1J53ANb5QXLjvETYP","content":[{"title":"Darwin-Gödel Machine: The First Self-Improving AI System Is Here","url":"https://www.intoai.pub/p/darwin-godel-machine-the-first-self"},{"title":"GitHub - lemoz/darwin-godel-machine: Self-improving AI agents implementing the Darwin Gödel Machine research paper. Features multi-LLM support, sandboxed execution, population-based evolution, and comprehensive benchmarking.","url":"https://github.com/lemoz/darwin-godel-machine"},{"title":"Darwin Gödel Machine: Self-Improving AI Agents - AI Papers Academy","url":"https://aipapersacademy.com/darwin-godel-machine/"},{"title":"Open ended algorithms: inside sakana’s darwin gödel machine | by Rick Boelen | Medium","url":"https://medium.com/@rickboelen98/open-ended-algorithms-inside-sakanas-darwin-g%C3%B6del-machine-a129a5fe5379"},{"title":"Sakana AI on X: \"Introducing The Darwin Gödel Machine: AI that improves itself by rewriting its own code https://t.co/tBzlhoUMZO The Darwin Gödel Machine (DGM) is a self-improving agent that can modify its own code. Inspired by evolution, we maintain an expanding lineage of agent variants, https://t.co/yIQ0w85N7U\" / X","url":"https://x.com/SakanaAILabs/status/1928272612431646943"},{"title":"The Darwin Gödel Machine: Open-Ended Improvement via Recursive Code Mutation and Empirical Fitness | by Adnan Masood, PhD. | Medium","url":"https://medium.com/@adnanmasood/the-darwin-g%C3%B6del-machine-open-ended-improvement-via-recursive-code-mutation-and-empirical-fitness-a777681d73e4"},{"title":"Darwin Gödel Machine - by Grigory Sapunov - Gonzo ML","url":"https://gonzoml.substack.com/p/darwin-godel-machine"},{"title":"Darwin Godel Machine: Open-Ended Evolution of Self-Improving Agents","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2505.22954"},{"title":"[2505.22954] Darwin Godel Machine: Open-Ended Evolution of Self-Improving Agents","url":"https://arxiv.org/abs/2505.22954"},{"title":"The Darwin Gödel Machine: AI that improves itself by rewriting its own code","url":"https://sakana.ai/dgm/"}]},"Based on the search results, here's what I found about the Darwin Gödel Machine paper:\n\n## Overview\n\nThe Darwin Gödel Machine (DGM) is a paper authored by Jenny Zhang and 4 other authors that introduces a self-improving AI system. The research paper is titled \"Darwin Gödel Machine: Open-Ended Evolution of Self-Improving Agents\" and is available on arXiv (arXiv:2505.22954).\n\n## What It Does\n\nThe Darwin-Gödel Machine is an architecture that can iteratively modify its own codebase to improve itself while continuously checking its performance on different coding benchmarks. This architecture is inspired by Darwinian evolutionary biology, in which multiple variants grow from a single starting point and the ones that perform the best \"survive\" most successfully.\n\n## Key Innovation\n\nThe DGM relaxes the Gödel Machine's impractical requirement of theoretically proving that a change will improve the system, instead requiring empirical evidence from experiments to demonstrate that a proposed new version enhances performance.\n\n## Results\n\nThe DGM automatically improves its coding capabilities, increasing performance on SWE-bench from 20.0% to 50.0%, and on Polyglot from 14.2% to 30.7%.\n\n## Team\n\nResearchers at Sakana AI, a Tokyo-based AI research lab, proposed this architecture, and the work was done in collaboration with Jeff Clune's lab at the University of British Columbia."],"durationSeconds":7.76902341600135,"searchCount":1},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"a7deb8e6-47c6-48da-869a-a95166ddb200","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
{"parentUuid":"6a010689-9dff-4f16-897c-4db1c99caeef","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"ad2e30b85cc1c5b90","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0116Cs8F17Hc7PtsFw1p9N84","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Darwin Godel Machine SWE-bench Polyglot score improvement results\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Darwin Gödel Machine: Self-Improving AI Agents - AI Papers Academy\",\"url\":\"https://aipapersacademy.com/darwin-godel-machine/\"},{\"title\":\"The Darwin Gödel Machine: AI that improves itself by rewriting its own code\",\"url\":\"https://sakana.ai/dgm/\"},{\"title\":\"Paper page - Darwin Godel Machine: Open-Ended Evolution of Self-Improving Agents\",\"url\":\"https://huggingface.co/papers/2505.22954\"},{\"title\":\"[2505.22954] Darwin Godel Machine: Open-Ended Evolution of Self-Improving Agents\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2505.22954\"},{\"title\":\"Darwin Gödel Machine: Open-Ended Evolution of Self-Improving Agents\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/html/2505.22954v2\"},{\"title\":\"The Darwin Gödel Machine: Open-Ended Improvement via Recursive Code Mutation and Empirical Fitness | by Adnan Masood, PhD. | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://medium.com/@adnanmasood/the-darwin-g%C3%B6del-machine-open-ended-improvement-via-recursive-code-mutation-and-empirical-fitness-a777681d73e4\"},{\"title\":\"ICLR Poster Darwin Gödel Machine: Open-Ended Evolution of Self-Improving Agents\",\"url\":\"https://iclr.cc/virtual/2026/poster/10007327\"},{\"title\":\"Darwin Gödel Machine: Open-Ended Evolution of Self-Improving Agents | OpenReview\",\"url\":\"https://openreview.net/forum?id=pUpzQZTvGY\"},{\"title\":\"Darwin Gödel Machine - by Grigory Sapunov - Gonzo ML\",\"url\":\"https://gonzoml.substack.com/p/darwin-godel-machine\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - jennyzzt/dgm: Darwin Gödel Machine: Open-Ended Evolution of Self-Improving Agents · GitHub\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/jennyzzt/dgm\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here are the key findings on Darwin Gödel Machine's SWE-bench and Polyglot score improvements:\n\n## SWE-bench Results\n\nOn SWE-bench, the DGM automatically improved its performance from 20.0% to 50.0%. This represents a success rate improvement that is comparable to state-of-the-art open-source solutions like OpenHands + CodeAct v2.1 at 53.0%.\n\n## Polyglot Results\n\nOn Polyglot, the DGM jumped performance from an initial 14.2% to 30.7%, which far surpasses the representative hand-designed agent by Aider.\n\n## Improvement Mechanisms\n\nThe DGM automatically improves its coding capabilities through the discovery of better code editing tools, long-context window management, and peer-review mechanisms. The DGM shows sustained improvement over 80 iterations, with performance curves demonstrating how open-ended exploration escapes deceptive local optima through temporary dips followed by breakthroughs.\n\n## Performance Comparison\n\nThe DGM significantly outperforms baselines without self-improvement or open-ended exploration, establishing that both components are essential for achieving these substantial gains.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"591e01b3-8783-4250-b82a-ef65411b9083","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:34:13.874Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"Darwin Godel Machine SWE-bench Polyglot score improvement results","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01NaBqUwL6PzZF2Gjb26zByc","content":[{"title":"Darwin Gödel Machine: Self-Improving AI Agents - AI Papers Academy","url":"https://aipapersacademy.com/darwin-godel-machine/"},{"title":"The Darwin Gödel Machine: AI that improves itself by rewriting its own code","url":"https://sakana.ai/dgm/"},{"title":"Paper page - Darwin Godel Machine: Open-Ended Evolution of Self-Improving Agents","url":"https://huggingface.co/papers/2505.22954"},{"title":"[2505.22954] Darwin Godel Machine: Open-Ended Evolution of Self-Improving Agents","url":"https://arxiv.org/abs/2505.22954"},{"title":"Darwin Gödel Machine: Open-Ended Evolution of Self-Improving Agents","url":"https://arxiv.org/html/2505.22954v2"},{"title":"The Darwin Gödel Machine: Open-Ended Improvement via Recursive Code Mutation and Empirical Fitness | by Adnan Masood, PhD. | Medium","url":"https://medium.com/@adnanmasood/the-darwin-g%C3%B6del-machine-open-ended-improvement-via-recursive-code-mutation-and-empirical-fitness-a777681d73e4"},{"title":"ICLR Poster Darwin Gödel Machine: Open-Ended Evolution of Self-Improving Agents","url":"https://iclr.cc/virtual/2026/poster/10007327"},{"title":"Darwin Gödel Machine: Open-Ended Evolution of Self-Improving Agents | OpenReview","url":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=pUpzQZTvGY"},{"title":"Darwin Gödel Machine - by Grigory Sapunov - Gonzo ML","url":"https://gonzoml.substack.com/p/darwin-godel-machine"},{"title":"GitHub - jennyzzt/dgm: Darwin Gödel Machine: Open-Ended Evolution of Self-Improving Agents · GitHub","url":"https://github.com/jennyzzt/dgm"}]},"Based on the search results, here are the key findings on Darwin Gödel Machine's SWE-bench and Polyglot score improvements:\n\n## SWE-bench Results\n\nOn SWE-bench, the DGM automatically improved its performance from 20.0% to 50.0%. This represents a success rate improvement that is comparable to state-of-the-art open-source solutions like OpenHands + CodeAct v2.1 at 53.0%.\n\n## Polyglot Results\n\nOn Polyglot, the DGM jumped performance from an initial 14.2% to 30.7%, which far surpasses the representative hand-designed agent by Aider.\n\n## Improvement Mechanisms\n\nThe DGM automatically improves its coding capabilities through the discovery of better code editing tools, long-context window management, and peer-review mechanisms. The DGM shows sustained improvement over 80 iterations, with performance curves demonstrating how open-ended exploration escapes deceptive local optima through temporary dips followed by breakthroughs.\n\n## Performance Comparison\n\nThe DGM significantly outperforms baselines without self-improvement or open-ended exploration, establishing that both components are essential for achieving these substantial gains."],"durationSeconds":7.384781999999658,"searchCount":1},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"6a010689-9dff-4f16-897c-4db1c99caeef","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
